# Layer boundaries

Allowed imports per layer:

| Layer | May import | Must not import |
|-------|------------|-----------------|
| `internal/api/handlers` | `internal/service`, `internal/domain`, `echo` | `internal/repository/*`, `gorm` |
| `internal/api/routes` | `internal/api/handlers`, `echo` | service, repository, domain |
| `internal/service` | `internal/repository/*`, `internal/domain` | `echo`, `net/http` |
| `internal/repository/postgres` | `internal/domain`, `gorm` | `internal/service`, `echo` |
| `internal/domain` | stdlib only (plus struct tags) | everything else |

## Rules

- Handlers return `echo.Context` JSON responses. They do not open transactions.
- Services own validation and orchestration. If a service needs multiple repos, inject them via the constructor.
- Repositories return `*domain.X` or `error`. They do not translate errors into HTTP codes.
- When adding a new domain model, also register it in `AutoMigrate` in `internal/repository/postgres/connection.go`.
